    "sources": ["BSL SignBank (UCL regional colour signs)", "Access BSL", "SignBSL", "Linguanaut"],
    "notes": [
      "Color signs have SIGNIFICANT regional variation across the UK",
      "Numbers 1-5 are universal across UK; regional variants start at 6",
      "Southern numbers use thumb as 6; Northern use little finger as 6",
      "BSL uses TWO-HANDED fingerspelling unlike ASL's one-handed system"
